Teach VUnit's GHDL backend detector about the `llvm-jit` backend.

GHDL has had four backends for a while: mcode, llvm, llvm-jit, gcc.
VUnit's `GHDLInterface.determine_backend` regex mapping only covers
three (mcode/llvm/gcc), so any GHDL built with `--with-backend=llvm-jit`
fails detection with

    AssertionError: No known GHDL back-end could be detected
    from running 'ghdl --version'

even though the binary works. The BCR `ghdl@6.0.0.bcr.1` module's
non-x86_64 builds select `llvm-jit` (because `mcode` is x86-only),
so the failure is observed end-to-end on aarch64 hosts running our
in-tree tests.

This patch adds an `llvm-jit` entry to the mapping. Treating it as a
distinct backend value (rather than collapsing it into `llvm`) keeps
the existing branches correct: `_has_output_flag` returns False for
JIT backends, and `supports_coverage` returns False because gcov
needs the gcc backend — both behaviours are right for `llvm-jit`.

Drop this patch when bumping to a VUnit release that recognises the
backend upstream.

diff --git a/vunit/sim_if/ghdl.py b/vunit/sim_if/ghdl.py
--- a/vunit/sim_if/ghdl.py
+++ b/vunit/sim_if/ghdl.py
@@ -128,6 +128,7 @@
         mapping = {
             r"mcode (JIT )?code generator": "mcode",
             r"llvm (\d+\.\d+\.\d+ )?code generator": "llvm",
+            r"LLVM JIT code generator": "llvm-jit",
             r"GCC (back-end|\d+\.\d+\.\d+) code generator": "gcc",
         }
         output = cls._get_version_output(prefix)
